Description: Fragment of neck and flattened handle of a pottery transport amphora to moderate turn. Clay medium-coarse red-brown. Circular stamp with Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary 1884-5 (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 201, 12 or 206, 9. Common type.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1326)
